Fancy seeing a pair of kiwi brawling in your garden! That's the sight that Kerikeri local Karin Matthews saw last week when she herd some strange noises coming from outside. We think the birds may have been fighting over food - and possibly coming out during the day to find food. Conditions are currently very dry in Northland at the moment which makes it much harder than normal for kiwi to forage for food. When the ground is hard and dry, they find it hard to probe into the ground to find food. And if they can't feed enough at night when they should be out and about, they have to try to feed during the day as well. Meta just invented artificial fingers (the digital fashion use case is wild). The project is called Digit360. Those little lights are super advanced digital fingertips. They pick up over 18 different attributes and can sense/react just like a human or animal would. For example, when it picks up something delicate, it knows how to adjust pressure to hold it carefully without breaking. Or if it feels something pointy, it can recoil immediately. But the coolest use case they teased was the future of digital fashion. In theory, a Digit360 scanner could be run across clothing and immediately be able to transmit the feeling of that material digitally. This means that brands could have mixed reality experiences where a user wearing haptic gloves could actually feel the texture, thickness, and quality of a garment from their couch. This is a bit of a futuristic example, but hints at where this is headed. Digit360 could also be super powerful if appended to the end of prosthetics, potentially giving more acute sensory feedback. Meta is currently working to scale the manufacturing of Digit360...I could see this giving way to an entirely new set of embodied experiences. The Chinese government's efforts to erase the memory of the Tiananmen Square Massacre are extensive and multifaceted. Since the tragic events of June 4, 1989, when the Chinese military violently suppressed pro-democracy protests, the government has consistently sought to censor any discussion or commemoration of the massacre. This includes imprisoning individuals in China and Hong Kong who attempt to honor the victims or acknowledge the event. The government has refused to take responsibility for the killings or provide redress to victims' families. Censorship is rigorously enforced through China's "Great Firewall," which blocks mentions of the massacre online. Social media platforms like Sina Weibo are heavily monitored, with posts related to Tiananmen being swiftly removed. In addition to online censorship, the Chinese Communist Party (CCP) has cultivated a form of cultural amnesia around the massacre. The event is not taught in schools, nor is it mentioned in official media outlets. As a result, many young people in China remain unaware of this significant historical event. The CCP's strategy has been to maintain its grip on power by suppressing political rights and controlling historical narratives. This approach has also been extended to Hong Kong, where authorities have removed books about the massacre from libraries and restricted public commemorations. Despite these efforts, the memory of Tiananmen persists among Chinese communities abroad and through international initiatives. For instance, the June 4 Memorial Museum in New York City serves as a permanent exhibition dedicated to preserving the history of the massacre and supporting pro-democracy movements. These global efforts highlight a continued resistance against Beijing's attempts to rewrite history and ensure that the legacy of Tiananmen remains alive outside China's borders. Sources: https://www.hrw.org/news/2024/06/02/china-closing-memory-tiananmen-massacre https://time.com/5571372/tiananmen-massacre-june-4-1989-china-censorship/ https://www.dailysignal.com/2024/06/04/35-years-after-tiananmen-square-beijing-still-tries-to-erase-memories/

Magnetic forces, like all electromagnetic forces, propagate at the speed of light, meaning that changes in a magnetic field can travel through space almost instantaneously on a human scale. However, when these forces interact with physical objects, the effect is not immediate acceleration to high velocities. Instead, objects respond to these forces gradually, in accordance with Newtonâ€™s second law of motion. This law states that the acceleration of an object is proportional to the force applied and inversely proportional to its mass. Therefore, even though the magnetic influence reaches the object almost instantly, the object itself accelerates slowly depending on the magnitude of the force and its own inertia. This interplay between the rapid propagation of electromagnetic forces and the gradual response of material objects reflects the fundamental principles of physics governing motion and force. Nissan is a Japanese multinational automobile manufacturer headquartered in Yokohama, Japan. Founded in 1933, Nissan has grown to become one of the largest and most well-known car brands globally. The company is renowned for its innovative approach to automotive design and technology. Nissan offers a wide range of vehicles, from compact cars and sedans to SUVs, trucks, and electric vehicles. One of its most famous models is the Nissan Leaf, a pioneering electric vehicle that has gained popularity for its affordability and eco-friendly features. Nissan is also known for its performance-oriented cars, such as the Nissan GT-R, which has a strong reputation in the sports car market. Hereâ€™s a classic brownie recipe that yields rich and fudgy brownies: ### Ingredients: - 1 cup (225g) unsalted butter - 1 cup (200g) granulated sugar - 1 cup (200g) brown sugar, packed - 4 large eggs - 1 teaspoon vanilla extract - 1 cup (125g) all-purpose flour - 1 cup (85g) unsweetened cocoa powder - 1/2 teaspoon salt - 1 cup (175g) chocolate chips or chunks (optional) ### Instructions: 1. **Preheat Oven**: Preheat your oven to 350Â°F (175Â°C). Grease a 9x13 inch baking pan or line it with parchment paper. 2. **Melt Butter**: In a medium saucepan, melt the butter over low heat. Once melted, remove from heat and let it cool slightly. 3. **Mix Sugars and Eggs**: In a large mixing bowl, combine the granulated sugar and brown sugar. Add the melted butter to the sugars and mix well. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in the vanilla extract. 4. **Combine Dry Ingredients**: In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, cocoa powder, and salt. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined. 5. **Add Chocolate Chips**: Fold in the chocolate chips or chunks if using. 6. **Bake**: Pour the batter into the prepared baking pan and spread it evenly. Bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out with a few moist crumbs (not wet batter). 7. **Cool and Serve**: Allow the brownies to cool completely in the pan before cutting into squares and serving. The electric motor assists the internal combustion engine during acceleration and also allows for electric-only driving at low speeds. 3. **Design**: Its design is highly aerodynamic and focused on maximizing downforce and minimizing drag. The LaFerrariâ€™s styling reflects Ferrariâ€™s commitment to both performance and aesthetics, with sharp lines and a low-slung profile. 4. **Limited Production**: Only 499 units were produced, making it a highly exclusive and sought-after vehicle among collectors and enthusiasts. Each LaFerrari was hand-built and customized to some extent according to the buyerâ€™s preferences. 5. **Technological Features**: It incorporates advanced technologies such as active aerodynamics, adaptive suspension, and extensive use of lightweight materials like carbon fiber to optimize performance and handling. Overall, the LaFerrari represents Ferrariâ€™s pinnacle of automotive engineering and performance, blending traditional V12 power with modern hybrid technology to create a hypercar that delivers exhilarating performance on both the road and the track.

recipe of the day ğŸ‘‡ Sticky Toffee Pudding **Ingredients:** **For the pudding:** - 200g dates, pitted and chopped - 300ml boiling water - 1 teaspoon baking soda - 85g unsalted butter, softened - 175g light brown sugar - 2 large eggs - 1 teaspoon vanilla extract - 200g self-raising flour - 1 teaspoon baking powder **For the toffee sauce:** - 200g light brown sugar - 100g unsalted butter - 300ml double cream - 1 tablespoon black treacle or golden syrup **Instructions:** 1. **Prepare the dates:** Preheat your oven to 180Â°C (350Â°F). Grease and line an 8-inch square baking dish. Place the chopped dates in a bowl, pour over the boiling water, and stir in the baking soda. Let it sit while you prepare the pudding batter. 2. **Make the batter:** In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar together until light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs one at a time, then add the vanilla extract. Sift in the flour and baking powder, then gently fold in the soaked dates and their liquid. 3. **Bake the pudding:** Pour the batter into the prepared baking dish and bake for 35-40 minutes, or until a skewer inserted into the center comes out clean. 4. **Make the toffee sauce:** While the pudding is baking, make the sauce. In a saucepan, combine the sugar, butter, cream, and treacle (or golden syrup). Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until the sugar has dissolved. Bring to a simmer and cook for 3-4 minutes until thickened slightly. 5. **Serve:** Once the pudding is done, poke holes all over the surface with a skewer or fork, and pour half of the toffee sauce over the top. Allow it to soak in for a few minutes. Serve warm, drizzled with the remaining sauce, and enjoy with a scoop of vanilla ice cream or whipped cream! Enjoy this rich and indulgent dessert!

Preheat your oven to 350Â°F (175Â°C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper. 2. In a large bowl, cream together the butter, white sugar, and brown sugar until smooth. 3. Creamy Garlic Parmesan Pasta Ingredients: â€¢ 8 oz fettuccine â€¢ 2 tbsp butter â€¢ 4 cloves garlic, minced â€¢ 1 cup heavy cream â€¢ 1 cup grated Parmesan cheese â€¢ 1/2 cup chicken broth â€¢ Salt and pepper to taste â€¢ Fresh parsley, chopped (for garnish) Instructions: 1. Cook the fettuccine according to package instructions. Drain and set aside. 2. In a large skillet, melt the butter over medium heat. Add the minced garlic and sautÃ© for 1-2 minutes until fragrant, but not browned. 3. Pour in the heavy cream and chicken broth, stirring to combine. Bring the mixture to a simmer. 4. Gradually whisk in the grated Parmesan cheese until the sauce is smooth and creamy. Season with salt and pepper to taste. 5. Hibernation is an adaptation for survival in harsh conditions like cold or food scarcity. Animals reduce metabolism, store fat, lower body temperature, slow breathing/heart rate, and seek insulated shelters. These mechanisms evolved to conserve energy and help animals endure tough times, emerging unharmed when conditions improve. Animals rely on stored energy, mainly fats, to endure food scarcity and harsh winters. Smaller mammals experience torpor, lowering body temperature with intermittent warming periods, while larger mammals maintain more stable temperatures. Literal brain rot To cook a tender steak, itâ€™s crucial to start with a good quality piece of meat. Look for cuts that are well-marbled with fat, such as ribeye or New York strip. Before cooking, allow the steak to come to room temperature, as this ensures even cooking. Season the steak generously with salt and pepper, or your preferred steak seasoning, and let it sit for at least 30 minutes to allow the flavors to penetrate the meat. For the cooking process, preheat a heavy skillet or grill pan over high heat. The pan should be hot enough that it sizzles when you place the steak on it. Sear the steak for a few minutes on each side to create a caramelized crust. Then, reduce the heat to medium and continue cooking to your desired level of doneness. Use a meat thermometer to achieve the perfect temperature: 120Â°F for rare, 130Â°F for medium-rare, 140Â°F for medium, and so on. Remember to let the steak rest for a few minutes before slicing it, as this allows the juices to redistribute and results in a more tender and flavorful steak. Another method to ensure a tender steak is to marinate it before cooking. Create a marinade using ingredients like olive oil, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, and herbs. Place the steak in a resealable bag and pour the marinade over it, making sure it is evenly coated. Let it marinate in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour, or overnight for maximum flavor. When itâ€™s time to cook, remove the steak from the marinade and pat it dry with paper towels. Discard the marinade as it may contain harmful bacteria. Preheat your grill or skillet over medium-high heat and cook the steak following the same searing and cooking instructions as mentioned before. The marinade not only adds flavor but also helps to tenderize the meat by breaking down the muscle fibers. By following these techniques, you can cook a steak that is not only delicious but also incredibly tender. Whether you choose to sear it or marinate it, remember that the key lies in using high-quality meat and giving it the proper time and attention it deserves. #reels #brainrot #dankmemes

No problem, hereâ€™s some information on the Mercedes-Benz CLR GTR is a notable racing car developed for the 1999 24 Hours of Le Mans by Mercedes-AMG. It was the successor to the successful CLK GTR and CLK LM models used in GT racing. The CLR GTR was designed with the goal of competing in the Le Mans Prototype (LMP) category, featuring a sleeker and more aerodynamic body than its predecessors. However, the CLR GTR is most famously remembered for its notorious incidents at the 1999 Le Mans race. During practice and the race itself, the CLR GTR experienced severe aerodynamic instability, leading to three separate instances where the car flipped into the air at high speeds. The most dramatic incident occurred during the race when driver Peter Dumbreckâ€™s car flipped and went airborne, landing in the trees. Fortunately, no drivers were seriously injured in these incidents. The aerodynamic issues were primarily due to the carâ€™s design, which created lift at high speeds, exacerbated by the undulating surface of the Le Mans circuit. These incidents led Mercedes-Benz to withdraw from the race and subsequently exit from Le Mans racing altogether for several years. Despite its advanced engineering and high potential, the CLR GTR is often remembered as a cautionary tale about the importance of aerodynamic stability in race car design. #meme #dark #darkmeme #jokesonyou #repost #edit #video #comments #trending #trendingvideos #humour #darkhumour #lilbro #fyp #ğŸ’€

classic String theory is a theoretical framework in physics that aims to reconcile general relativity and quantum mechanics, the two pillars of modern physics. At its core, string theory proposes that the fundamental building blocks of the universe are not point-like particles, but rather one-dimensional â€œstringsâ€ that vibrate at specific frequencies. These vibrations determine the properties of particles, such as mass and charge, much like the different notes produced by a vibrating guitar string ğŸ¸. One of the most intriguing aspects of string theory is its requirement for additional dimensions beyond the familiar three dimensions of space and one dimension of time. In fact, string theory suggests the existence of up to 11 dimensions! These extra dimensions are thought to be compactified or curled up so small that they are not easily observable in our everyday experience ğŸŒ€. String theory has also given rise to the concept of â€œbranes,â€ multi-dimensional objects on which strings can attach. Our entire universe could be a 3-dimensional brane floating in a higher-dimensional space, with other branes potentially hosting parallel universes ğŸª. Despite its elegance and potential, string theory remains highly speculative. It has yet to produce testable predictions that can be experimentally verified. Nonetheless, it offers a tantalizing glimpse into the deeper structure of reality and continues to inspire physicists in their quest for a unified theory of everything. Whether or not string theory ultimately proves correct, its influence on theoretical physics and the way we think about the universe is undeniable. ğŸŒŒâœ¨

Hereâ€™s a classic brownie recipe that yields rich and fudgy brownies: ### Ingredients: - 1 cup (225g) unsalted butter - 1 cup (200g) granulated sugar - 1 cup (200g) brown sugar, packed - 4 large eggs - 1 teaspoon vanilla extract - 1 cup (125g) all-purpose flour - 1 cup (85g) unsweetened cocoa powder - 1/2 teaspoon salt - 1 cup (175g) chocolate chips or chunks Instructions: 1. **Preheat Oven**: Preheat your oven to 350Â°F (175Â°C). Grease a 9x13 inch baking pan or line it with parchment paper. 2. **Melt Butter**: In a medium saucepan, melt the butter over low heat. Once melted, remove from heat and let it cool slightly. 3. **Mix Sugars and Eggs**: In a large mixing bowl, combine the granulated sugar and brown sugar. Add the melted butter to the sugars and mix well. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in the vanilla extract. 4. **Combine Dry Ingredients**: In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, cocoa powder, and salt. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined. 5. **Add Chocolate Chips**: Fold in the chocolate chips or chunks if using. 6. **Bake**: Pour the batter into the prepared baking pan and spread it evenly. Bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out with a few moist crumbs (not wet batter). 7. **Cool and Serve**: Allow the brownies to cool completely in the pan before cutting into squares and serving.

shocking String theory is a theoretical framework in which the point-like particles of particle physics are replaced by one-dimensional objects known as strings. These strings can vibrate at different frequencies, and their different vibrational modes are thought to correspond to the various fundamental particles observed in nature. This idea emerged in the late 20th century as physicists sought to reconcile general relativity, which describes gravity at macroscopic scales, with quantum mechanics, which explains the behavior of particles at microscopic scales. One of the most compelling features of string theory is its potential to unify all the fundamental forces of natureâ€”gravitational, electromagnetic, strong, and weak interactionsâ€”into a single theoretical framework. This has led some to dub it a â€œtheory of everythingâ€ ğŸŒŒ. In addition, string theory requires extra spatial dimensions beyond the familiar three. These additional dimensions are theorized to be compactified or curled up in such a way that they are not observable at everyday energy scales. String theory also introduces the concept of supersymmetry, a proposed symmetry between bosons and fermions. This theoretical symmetry could solve many puzzles in particle physics and cosmology, including the hierarchy problem and the nature of dark matter. Despite its elegance and mathematical beauty, string theory remains a topic of active research and debate within the scientific community due to the current lack of experimental evidence ğŸ§©. The development and exploration of string theory continue to push the boundaries of our understanding of the universe, offering tantalizing possibilities for a more profound comprehension of the cosmos and its underlying principles âœ¨.

Peter ğŸ’€ Follow @daily_griffin_clips_ for daily dose of laughter The Great Blue Hole in Belize is one of the most fascinating natural wonders on Earth. Located about 70 kilometers (43 miles) from the mainland and Belize City, this giant marine sinkhole is a part of the Lighthouse Reef, a small atoll that is part of the larger Belize Barrier Reef Reserve System, a UNESCO World Heritage Site. The Blue Hole is almost perfectly circular, with a diameter of over 300 meters (984 feet) and a depth of 125 meters (410 feet). The sinkhole was formed during several episodes of quaternary glaciation when sea levels were much lower. As the sea levels rose, the caves were flooded, creating the Blue Hole we see today. Its deep blue color stands in stark contrast to the lighter, turquoise waters of the surrounding shallow reefs, creating a dramatic and visually striking phenomenon. The Great Blue Hole is a mecca for scuba divers, who come from all over the world to explore its depths. Divers are drawn to the crystal-clear waters, the impressive stalactites and stalagmites that can be found at depths of 30 meters (100 feet) and deeper, and the diverse marine life that inhabits the area. Species such as nurse sharks, giant groupers, and various types of reef sharks, including the Caribbean reef shark, can be found within the Blue Hole. In addition to its natural beauty, the Blue Hole has significant scientific value. It offers researchers insights into the geological and climatic history of the region, as the stalactites and stalagmites provide clues about the Earth's past sea levels and climate conditions. The formations found within the sinkhole suggest that it was once a dry cave system, now submerged due to rising sea levels. #familyguy #petergriffin #stewiegriffin #funnyshit #explorepageready #explorepage #lmaoğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ #laughoutloud #funnyclips #funnyvideos#comedyvideos #comedyvideo #comedymemes #familyguymemes #dankmemesdaily #dankvideos #humourous #hahaha #meggriffin

Sure, here's a simple recipe for homemade chocolate fudge: ### Ingredients: - 2 cups semi-sweet chocolate chips - 1 (14-ounce) can sweetened condensed milk - 1/4 cup unsalted butter - 1 teaspoon vanilla extract - Pinch of salt - Optional: 1/2 cup chopped nuts (like walnuts or pecans) ### Instructions: 1. **Prepare the Pan**: Line an 8-inch square baking pan with parchment paper or aluminum foil, leaving some overhang on the sides. This will make it easier to lift the fudge out later. 2. **Melt the Ingredients**: In a medium saucepan over low heat, combine the chocolate chips, sweetened condensed milk, and butter. Stir constantly until the chocolate and butter are completely melted and the mixture is smooth. 3. **Add Vanilla and Salt**: Remove the saucepan from the heat and stir in the vanilla extract and a pinch of salt. If you are adding nuts, fold them in at this point. 4. **Pour into Pan**: Pour the fudge mixture into the prepared pan, spreading it out evenly with a spatula. 5. **Chill**: Let the fudge cool to room temperature, then refrigerate it for at least 2 hours or until it is firm. 6. **Cut and Serve**: Lift the fudge out of the pan using the parchment paper overhang. Cut it into small squares with a sharp knife. ### Tips: - For a different flavor, you can add a teaspoon of instant coffee granules to the mixture while melting. - For a festive touch, sprinkle crushed peppermint candies or sea salt on top of the fudge before it sets. Enjoy your homemade chocolate fudge! #funny #viral #fyp #brainrot #global

The copper provides an initial path to ground for the electricity, and because the voltage is so high (on the order of a hundred thousand) that the copper vaporizes almost instantly. The copper and the air around it are ionized by the heat, making the air itself conductive. This can happen spontaneously in the case of lightning or other arcing if the voltage is high enough or the gap is small enough (the breakdown voltage of dry air is something like 10,000 volts per centimeter). The power line is engineered such that everything has enough separation distance to prevent this, but the copper bridges the gap. What you see is Plasma, the fourth state of matter. Plasma is an ionized gas consisting of approximately equal numbers of positively and negatively charged particles. Additionally, the lightning seen in thunderstorms is another form of plasma. Lightning is caused by electricity traveling through the air and ionizing the areas it travels through, creating a great conductor path.
